{
  "texts": [
    "MG-DDIS model (Deng et al.",
    "2021) is an end-to-end multi-task learning framework based on a GCN for predicting DDIs and synergistic drug combinations.",
    "The model to capture important information from the molecular structures, the R-radius subgraph method is applied, producing a series of subgraphs for each drug.",
    "These subgraphs are then fed into the GCN encoder to learn a latent representation of drugs.",
    "The model is trained using a multi-task approach to simultaneously predict DDIs and synergistic drug combinations."
  ]
}